 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.375","title":"[audit][websocket] Accept standard wire close codes 1012/1013/1014","description":"Fresh audit follow-up for the websocket close-code surface. Current CloseCode validation rejects assigned wire codes 1012, 1013, and 1014, which means outbound Frame::close panics on them and inbound close handshakes reject peers that use them. Narrow fix: extend the close-code enum/validation/tests without changing framing state machines.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ubuntu","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:37:21.086898051Z","created_by":"BronzeBrook","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:55:20.464227222Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T04:55:20.464196746Z","close_reason":"Fixed: test updated for IANA-registered codes 1012-1014, added sendable/from_u16/valid_code tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","net","protocol","websocket"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.375","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:37:21.086898051Z","created_by":"BronzeBrook"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.376","title":"[audit][quic] Make repeated begin_close/draining idempotent","description":"Fresh audit follow-up for src/net/quic_native/transport.rs. Re-entering draining currently rewrites the drain deadline and can overwrite the close code, so repeated graceful-close calls are not a true no-op. Narrow fix: preserve the first drain deadline/code and add regressions for repeated begin_close while already draining.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"ChartreuseFalcon","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:37:38.133706284Z","created_by":"BronzeBrook","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:55:20.643395050Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T04:55:20.464692687Z","close_reason":"Fixed: start_draining made idempotent, preserves original deadline and close code","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","net","quic","shutdown"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.376","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:37:38.133706284Z","created_by":"BronzeBrook"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.377","title":"[audit][grpc] Make Channel::connect fail closed for non-loopback URIs","description":"src/grpc/client.rs currently accepts arbitrary http:// and https:// channel URIs in Channel::connect_with_config(), but the client implementation is still loopback-only: connect_with_config() only validates/stores the URI and GrpcClient::build_outbound_metadata() stamps x-asupersync-grpc-transport=loopback. This makes Channel::connect("http://real-host:50051") look like a real network connection even though no transport exists. Fail closed by rejecting non-loopback targets until a real transport is implemented, add focused regressions for accepted loopback hosts and rejected remote hosts, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"NavyHarbor","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:48:22.725847727Z","created_by":"NavyHarbor","updated_at":"2026-03-16T04:48:22.725847727Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.377","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T04:48:22.725847727Z","created_by":"NavyHarbor"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.378","title":"[audit][grpc/server] Do not treat malformed grpc-timeout as absent when default_timeout is configured","description":"CallContext::from_metadata_at currently falls back to default_timeout when a grpc-timeout header is present but malformed, even though the documented contract says the default only applies when the header is absent. Fix the fail-open behavior and add regression coverage.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AzureBay","created_at":"2026-03-16T06:33:15.440616656Z","created_by":"AzureBay","updated_at":"2026-03-16T06:33:15.440616656Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.378","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T06:33:15.440616656Z","created_by":"AzureBay"}]}
+{"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.379","title":"[audit][distributed/distribution] Report symbols_distributed from actual replica sends","description":"DistributionResult currently reports symbols_distributed from encoded.symbols.len() even when no replicas were targeted or assignments sent fewer total symbols across replica attempts. Make the reported count follow the actual computed send plan and add focused regressions.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"AzureBay","created_at":"2026-03-16T06:46:36.680605818Z","created_by":"AzureBay","updated_at":"2026-03-16T06:46:36.680605818Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","distributed"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.379","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-16T06:46:36.680605818Z","created_by":"AzureBay","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.38","title":"[audit][rate_limit] Restore consumed rate-limit token if guarded operation or web handler panics","description":"Both the core combinator and the sync web adapter consume a rate-limit token before invoking user code. In src/combinator/rate_limit.rs, RateLimiter::call_weighted() acquires tokens and then runs op() without an unwind guard, so a synchronous panic burns tokens even though the operation never completed. In src/web/middleware.rs, RateLimitMiddleware::call() uses limiter.try_acquire() and then calls the inner handler directly, so a panicking handler leaks the consumed token in the same way. Add a narrow refund path for panic unwind, route the web middleware through the panic-safe helper, add focused regression coverage in both modules, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"PinkForest","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:29:33.537070930Z","created_by":"PinkForest","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:50:02.362203392Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:50:02.362173717Z","close_reason":"Refund consumed rate-limit tokens on synchronous panic in combinator and web middleware; focused rch regressions passed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","combinator","rate-limit","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.38","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:29:33.537070930Z","created_by":"PinkForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","title":"[audit][grpc] Make tracing interceptor request IDs deterministic","description":"src/grpc/interceptor.rs currently generates x-request-id values from SystemTime::now(), which makes request IDs nondeterministic and introduces ambient wall-clock authority into library code. Replace that clock-based ID generation with a deterministic interceptor-owned source, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted check/clippy/test commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaHollow","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T02:30:28.727934377Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:38.909958605Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:38.909932226Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","grpc"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:30:28.727934377Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2460,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.39","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Replaced TracingInterceptor request ID generation in src/grpc/interceptor.rs with a deterministic interceptor-owned AtomicU64 counter shared across clones, preserving caller-supplied x-request-id values and removing ambient SystemTime usage. Added focused regressions tracing_interceptor_uses_deterministic_sequential_ids and tracing_interceptor_preserves_existing_request_id. Validation: rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/grpc/interceptor.rs ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-check cargo check -p asupersync --lib ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-clippy cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings ✅; rch exec -- env TMPDIR=/data/projects/asupersync CARGO_TARGET_DIR=/data/projects/asupersync/target-rch-fuchsia-grpc-test cargo test -p asupersync --lib tracing_interceptor_ -- --nocapture ✅ (3 passed).","created_at":"2026-03-09T02:37:32Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.4","title":"[audit][service] Reserve buffer capacity in poll_ready so clone races cannot revoke readiness","description":"Buffer::poll_ready currently reports Ready based only on the shared pending count, but it does not actually reserve a slot. Two clones can both observe Ready against capacity=1, after which one caller can fill the buffer and make the other caller's immediately-following call() fail with BufferError::Full. That violates the usual Service contract expectation that a successful poll_ready authorizes the next call on that handle. Fix by reserving a slot during poll_ready, consuming it in call(), releasing it on drop/close, and adding clone-race regression tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CloudyPond","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:50:03.548796130Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-08T02:08:16.874795269Z","closed_at":"2026-03-08T02:08:16.874685616Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","buffer","service"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.4","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-08T01:50:03.548796130Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
