 {"id":"asupersync-35wmm","title":"Trace normalization: canonical form for equivalent executions","description":"# Trace Normalization Implementation

## Goal

Implement trace normalization to convert execution traces into canonical form, enabling comparison of equivalent executions and efficient deduplication.

## Background

Two traces are equivalent if they differ only in the order of independent operations. Normalization picks one canonical representative per equivalence class.

Benefits:
- Deduplicate explored schedules
- Compare traces for equality
- Identify truly distinct behaviors
- Compress trace storage

## Mazurkiewicz Traces

A Mazurkiewicz trace is an equivalence class of sequences under:
- Swap adjacent independent operations

Example:
```
[a, b, c] ~ [b, a, c]  (if a, b independent)
```

## Independence Relation

Operations are independent if reordering doesn't change outcome:
```rust
pub trait Independence {
    fn independent(&self, op1: &Operation, op2: &Operation) -> bool;
}

impl Independence for AsupersyncSemantics {
    fn independent(&self, op1: &Operation, op2: &Operation) -> bool {
        // Different tasks
        if op1.task == op2.task { return false; }

        // No shared resource access
        match (&op1.kind, &op2.kind) {
            (Read(l1), Read(l2)) => true,  // Both reads: independent
            (Read(l1), Write(l2)) => l1 \!= l2,
            (Write(l1), Write(l2)) => l1 \!= l2,
            (Send(c1), Send(c2)) => c1 \!= c2,
            (Recv(c1), Recv(c2)) => c1 \!= c2,
            // ... other cases
        }
    }
}
```

## Normalization Algorithm

### Foata Normal Form
Group operations into 'steps' where all operations in a step are independent:
```
Step 1: [a, b, c]  (all pairwise independent)
Step 2: [d, e]     (all independent, but depend on step 1)
Step 3: [f]        (depends on step 2)
```

```rust
pub fn foata_normalize(trace: &Trace, indep: &impl Independence) -> FoataTrace {
    let mut steps = Vec::new();
    let mut remaining: HashSet<EventId> = trace.events.keys().collect();

    while \!remaining.is_empty() {
        // Find all events with no unprocessed dependencies
        let ready: Vec<_> = remaining.iter()
            .filter(|e| trace.deps_of(e).all(|d| \!remaining.contains(&d)))
            .cloned()
            .collect();

        // Group ready events by mutual independence
        let step = maximal_independent_set(&ready, indep);
        steps.push(step.clone());

        for e in step {
            remaining.remove(&e);
        }
    }

    FoataTrace { steps }
}
```

### Lexicographic Normal Form
Within each Foata step, sort events lexicographically:
```rust
impl FoataTrace {
    fn canonicalize(&mut self) {
        for step in &mut self.steps {
            step.sort_by_key(|e| (e.task.0, e.kind.discriminant(), e.data));
        }
    }
}
```

## TraceNormalizer

```rust
pub struct TraceNormalizer {
    /// Independence relation
    indep: Box<dyn Independence>,

    /// Normalization form
    form: NormalizationForm,
}

pub enum NormalizationForm {
    /// Foata normal form (partial order)
    Foata,

    /// Lexicographic (total order within Foata steps)
    Lexicographic,

    /// Hash-based (for comparison only)
    Hash,
}

impl TraceNormalizer {
    /// Normalize a trace
    fn normalize(&self, trace: &Trace) -> NormalizedTrace;

    /// Check if two traces are equivalent
    fn equivalent(&self, t1: &Trace, t2: &Trace) -> bool;

    /// Compute canonical hash for a trace
    fn hash(&self, trace: &Trace) -> TraceHash;
}
```

## NormalizedTrace

```rust
pub struct NormalizedTrace {
    /// Original trace
    original: Trace,

    /// Foata form
    foata: FoataTrace,

    /// Canonical hash
    hash: TraceHash,
}

impl NormalizedTrace {
    /// Get the partial order (DAG of dependencies)
    fn partial_order(&self) -> &DependencyGraph;

    /// Get one linearization
    fn linearization(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = Event>;

    /// Count distinct linearizations
    fn linearization_count(&self) -> usize;
}
```

## Trace Comparison

```rust
impl PartialEq for NormalizedTrace {
    fn eq(&self, other: &Self) -> bool {
        self.hash == other.hash && self.foata == other.foata
    }
}

impl Hash for NormalizedTrace {
    fn hash<H: Hasher>(&self, state: &mut H) {
        self.hash.hash(state);
    }
}
```

## Integration with DPOR

```rust
impl ScheduleExplorer {
    /// Check if we've already explored an equivalent schedule
    fn already_explored(&self, trace: &Trace) -> bool {
        let normalized = self.normalizer.normalize(trace);
        self.explored_hashes.contains(&normalized.hash)
    }

    /// Record explored trace
    fn record_exploration(&mut self, trace: &Trace) {
        let normalized = self.normalizer.normalize(trace);
        self.explored_hashes.insert(normalized.hash);
    }
}
```

## Performance

Normalization is potentially expensive (computing dependencies). Optimizations:
1. Incremental: normalize as trace is built
2. Lazy: only normalize when needed for comparison
3. Hash-only: compute hash without full normalization

## Testing

- Simple traces with known equivalence
- Verify same hash for equivalent traces
- Different hash for non-equivalent traces
- Foata form correctness
- Performance with large traces

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Independence trait and implementation
- [ ] Foata normal form algorithm
- [ ] Lexicographic ordering within steps
- [ ] TraceNormalizer with all forms
- [ ] NormalizedTrace with hash/equality
- [ ] Integration with ScheduleExplorer
- [ ] Performance optimization
- [ ] Tests for equivalence and non-equivalence","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-31T21:27:50.331797873Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-02T06:42:22.050413756Z","closed_at":"2026-02-02T06:42:22.050265300Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["dpor","phase5","traces"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-35wmm","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3w01d","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:31Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-35wmm","depends_on_id":"asupersync-yguo9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:30:31Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
