-{"id":"asupersync-n6kwt","title":"[WASM] Feasible-browser parity closure beyond Browser Edition v1","description":"Browser Edition is now real and usable for JS/TS consumers, but it is still a bounded v1 subset: single-threaded, event-loop-driven, and centered on main-thread browser execution with direct fetch/WebSocket support. The next frontier is not to chase impossible native parity; it is to deliberately close every meaningful gap that the modern browser security model actually permits.

